5:
Good work at the ceremony,
Captain. Your address was quite
exemplary.
9:
I wish you wouldn't tease me... It was
almost like a parade out
thereâ€”completely unnecessary.
13:
But it was necessary. The Swallow
Knights just saved the kingdom,

16:
As the ones who brought everything
to a close, you stand as the one
symbol for their eyes to gaze upon.
20:
Anyway, why did you call me here
and order everyone else out?
23:
...Is there something we need to
discuss?
27:
Yes. I thought I should speak with
you about our future.
30: The truth is, after securing Marden...
37:
Between the monster assault and
the truth about Etheria's murder, I'm
afraid things are about to get rather
frantic...
40:
Firstly, we must investigate the
Kweturs and Oxtans. Until the root of

44:
The Kweturs will likely suffer the

47:
A single wrong move could spell
disaster.
51:
I am fully aware. His Highness also
wishes things to proceed righteously.
54:
...What will you do from this point on,
Cieldeau?
58:
My father has already made his
wishes clear. "Your blade shall
remain sheathed now."
62:
...And so, you must obey your
master. Are you quite sure you can
fully accept that?
66:
Whatever the case, my movements
are restricted for now.
69:
While you and the Swallow Knights
may be in Lord Varen's circle, I am
not.
73:
I assume he is not to your liking.
Easy to deal with, but too
straightforward.
77:
It's time to stop relying so much on
the House of Swes. Tris is even
thinking of supporting the prince's
claim...
81:
...What is it? Perhaps you had some
ill thought just now?
85:
No. I just realized I should learn from
Yuwel and His Highness...
88:
...By extending a hand to those who
shrink in the light. I can do that, as
well.
94:
Thank you for coming all this way,
Lornite Nialas.
97:
First, let me apologize for asking you
to come without any retainers.
Please forgive me for such a request.
100:
...I'm not interested in hollow words.
You seek information on the
Kweturs, I take it?
102:
Sorry, but I'm not about to turn my
back on my supporters. I will not
allow Tris toâ€”
106:
Then, why not allow House Tris to
support you instead?
109:
At the moment, Kwetur doesn't have
the power to aid you. In fact, they
might become your shackles...
112:
Will you not help us in cleansing the
rot? In time, Tris can become not
only your sword, but your shield as
well.
118:
Rebuilding the Nine Houses and
dispelling the darkness from the
Farlands.
121:
At the moment, my options are
limited, but... I want to break free of
those limitations.
124:
This is for the sake of everyone in the
Farlands. Will you take the hand I
offer you?
127:
...Lies, all of it. You're no different
from the Kweturs.
129:
That dirty look in your eyes tells me
you're looking to use me.
132: In that case, use me as well.
135:
If you have come because you, like
me, wish to reach the pinnacle of
light...
138:
...Then wield me at your leisure, Your
Highness, even if it be through mud.
141:
...I truly do not know much that
would be of value.
144:
I assumed as much, but there are
things only you can do while you
have the support of Kwetur.
147:
You sure do talk a lot for a
swordsman...
149:
...Very well. It never felt right that
Varen should be the only one
receiving favor.
160:
As I just explained, I won't be
supporting Prince Varen. That's my
plan.
165:
I mean it, WHAT were you thinking?! I
thought swordsmen don't talk, yet
you seem to be doing a lot of it!
168:
Forget the other housesâ€”if House
Tris finds out what you've done...
172:
I believe it was you and His Highness
that insisted I speak, no?
175:
Just as you said, I've stopped
putting up a front. I want to see how
far my blade will take me.
178:
This is all thanks to you. It is rather
enjoyable.
186:
Unfortunately, I still can't be seen
making such moves. My options
remain limited.
189:
So, I have a request for you. Will you
introduce me to your friends from
afar?
193: ...Is that why you've told me all of this?
197:
I merely wanted to share my plan so
that we can decide what to do
together and where the boundaries
fall.
200:
Let us work together, Yuwel Nouin.
You certainly cannot say you have
no interest in politics at this point.
204:
You wanted to visit with your sister...
If we tell them that, my friends will
allow it.
208:
Indeed, that's true. You have my
thanks, Yuwel.
211:
I shall prepare. You should hurry
along, too.
215:
Must it be right away? The
ceremony has only just ended.
219:
Of course, I am a busy man! It
seems I shall have MORE
disagreeable people to deal with.
223:
You do realize, Ciel, that your
attitude is absolutely appalling, yes?
227:
I can think of no higher praise. After
all, isn't that necessary for a
politician?
232:
Well... I suppose Alk and the others
can handle him... Just don't go
provoking him...
